  <h1>Contact</h1>
  <p class="lede">Feedback, corrections, a ghazal you&rsquo;d like to see, or a better reading of a line &mdash; all of it is welcome.</p>
</div>

<div class="ornament">About</div>

<div class="page-prose">
  <p>dharwism is a small, personal collection &mdash; ghazals written out to sing from, with the difficult words explained, and short notes on the ragas that hold them. It grows slowly, a poem and a raga at a time.</p>

  <p>Much of this is a labour of love around Urdu and the ghazal tradition. If you spot an error in a transliteration, know a finer rendition of a ghazal, or can shed light on a couplet, I&rsquo;d genuinely like to hear from you &mdash; corrections from careful listeners are the best thing that can happen to a page like this.</p>

  <p class="contact-line">
    <a id="email-link" class="email-btn" href="#">Email me</a>
  </p>
  <p class="contact-fallback" id="email-fallback" hidden></p>
</div>

<script>
  // Assemble the address at runtime so it isn't sitting in the HTML for scrapers.
  (function () {
    var user = "navrehcom";
    var domain = "gmail.com";
    var addr = user + "@" + domain;
    var subject = encodeURIComponent("dharwism — feedback");
    var link = document.getElementById("email-link");
    if (link) {
      link.href = "mailto:" + addr + "?subject=" + subject;
    }
    // Also reveal a readable address for those who prefer to copy it.
    var fb = document.getElementById("email-fallback");
    if (fb) {
      fb.textContent = addr;
      fb.hidden = false;
    }
  })();
</script>
